subSubSection.paragraph:
[Genus 
Liebstadia OUDEMANS
]

(a) the species with large body size, dorsoventrally thick, with a longer sensillus stalk and moreless lanceolate sensillus head (e.g. 
L. similis
).

In addition to the two mentioned forms intermediates could also be found (e.g. 
L. pannonica
). Probably, the life-form (a) belongs to the species living in the litter, soil surface or surface layer of the soil, and the life-form (b) seems to be an adaption for life in flat moss/lichen growths or the crevices and slots of tree bark. The intermediate forms were found mostly in grasslands or in shrub formations.
